fn main() => Binary{8} = not(0b1011_0010);" , fragment : Fragment :: BitSubset , note : "single unary bit op" , } , Case { id : "bit-xor-not" , src : "nodule d;
fn main() => Binary{8} = not(xor(0b1011_0010, 0b1111_1111));" , fragment : Fragment :: BitSubset , note : "a small straight-line bit pipeline (the xtask-e1 §2 shape)" , } , Case { id : "bit-let-chain" , src : "nodule d;
fn main() => Binary{8} =
  let a = 0b1011_0010 in let b = xor(a, 0b0000_1111) in not(xor(b, a));" , fragment : Fragment :: BitSubset , note : "let-bound straight-line bit computation (a few surface ops: not/xor only)" , } , Case { id : "trit-neg" , src : "nodule d;
fn main() => Ternary{4} = neg(0t00+-);" , fragment : Fragment :: BitSubset , note : "element-wise trit negation (the only trit op the MLIR-dialect path lowers)" , } , Case { id : "trit-add" , src : "nodule d;
fn main() => Ternary{4} = add(0t00+-, 0t0+0-);" , fragment : Fragment :: BitSubset , note : "balanced-ternary ripple-carry add (direct-LLVM lowers it; MLIR-dialect does NOT — a capability split)" , } , Case { id : "swap-roundtrip" , src : "nodule d;
fn main() => Binary{8} =
  let b = 0b0010_1010 in swap(swap(b, to: Ternary{6}, policy: rt), to: Binary{8}, policy: rt);" , fragment : Fragment :: Swap , note : "a binary->ternary->binary certified round-trip over a LEGAL (8,6) pair — since \
                   M-852 the compiled backends natively lower this to a value (measured, not \
